soln_description:
Solution. Let $n^{2}+2002 n=a^{2}, a \in \mathbb{N}$. Then $a=n+k$ for some $k \in \mathbb{N}$, so

$$
\begin{aligned}
& n^{2}+2002 n=(n+k)^{2} \\
& 2002 n-2 n k=k^{2} \\
& n=\frac{k^{2}}{2002-2 k}=\frac{k^{2}}{2(1001-k)}
\end{aligned}
$$

From the last equality, it follows that $k=2 m$ for some $m \in \mathbb{N}$, which means $n=\frac{2 m^{2}}{1001-2 m}$. Clearly, $1001-2 m>0$, so $m \leq 500$. Now, the largest natural number $n$ is obtained when in $n=\frac{2 m^{2}}{1001-2 m}$ we have the largest numerator and the smallest denominator, which is for $m=500$. Finally, the desired number is $n=\frac{2 \cdot 500^{2}}{1001-2 \cdot 500}=500000$.

20. (1) Let the annual income at the end of each year be $A$ million yuan, with an annual profit of $10\%$, then:
the income from the first year's $A$ million yuan to the $n$-th year is $Q_{1}=A(1+0.1)^{n-1}$;
the income from the second year's $A$ million yuan to the $n$-th year is $Q_{2}=A(1+0.1)^{n-2}$;
the income from the $(n-1)$-th year's $A$ million yuan to the $n$-th year is $Q_{n-1}=A(1+0.1)$;
the income from the $n$-th year is $Q_{n}=A(1+0.1)^{0}=A$.
$Q_{1}, Q_{2} \cdots Q_{n}$ form a geometric sequence. Using the sum formula for a geometric sequence, the total income over these $n$ years is:
$$
Q=Q_{1}+Q_{2}+\cdots+Q_{n-1}+Q_{n}=\sum_{i=1}^{n} A(1+0.1)^{i-1}=\frac{A}{0.1}\left[(1+0.1)^{n}-1\right] \text {. }
$$

When $n=3$, $A=400$, $Q=\frac{400}{0.1} \cdot\left[(1+0.1)^{3}-1\right]=1324$ (million yuan). That is, the income after 3 years is 1324 million yuan, so 1300 million yuan can be obtained after 3 years.
(2) To recover the entire investment within 3 years, i.e., $Q=1600$, then $1600=\frac{A}{0.1}\left[(1+0.1)^{3}-1\right]$, solving for $A \approx 483.4$ (million yuan).
That is, an annual income of at least 483.4 million yuan is required to recover the entire investment within three years.

informal_statement:
Every time Joãozinho goes to the cinema, he drinks two soft drinks. He spent all his allowance of R$ 50.00 going to the cinema six times and drinking a total of 20 soft drinks, including those he drank when he went to the cinema. If Joãozinho had only one soft drink each time he went to the cinema, with this savings he could have gone to the cinema one more time, also drinking one soft drink on that occasion. Regarding the price of the cinema ticket and the price of the soft drink, we can state that

(a) the price of the ticket is three times the price of the soft drink;

(b) the price of the ticket is four times the price of the soft drink;

(c) the price of the ticket is five times the price of the soft drink;

(d) the ticket is R$ 6.00 more expensive than the soft drink;

(e) the ticket is R$ 5.00 more expensive than the soft drink.

